<linker>
  <!-- Force-preserve the WebRTC streamer assembly. We previously dropped this,
       trusting WebRTCStreamerBootstrap's [RuntimeInitializeOnLoadMethod] to be an
       IL2CPP root that survives on its own. iOS device builds proved that wrong:
       the assembly is autoReferenced:false with no inbound managed reference, so
       IL2CPP stripped it whole — the bootstrap never ran, the managed streamer
       factory was never registered, and live streaming 501'd
       ("WebRTCStreamerBootstrap did not run … stripped by IL2CPP"). Preserving the
       assembly keeps the bootstrap + WebRTCStreamer and lets the runtime-init hook
       fire on both mobile lanes. (No effect on Editor/Standalone — Mono doesn't
       strip.) com.unity.webrtc still ships its own link.xml for the Unity.WebRTC
       runtime itself. -->
  <assembly fullname="ODDGames.BugpunchSdk.WebRTC" preserve="all"/>

  <!-- Preserve [Watch] attribute and enum so IL2CPP doesn't strip them off
       user fields. Without this, declared-watch discovery silently finds nothing.
       NOTE: this package link.xml is NOT reliably honored for the SDK when it's
       consumed as an embedded `file:` package (the iOS IL2CPP strip ignored it —
       both this assembly and the WebRTC one were stripped despite preserve="all").
       The native-init survival is therefore enforced with [AlwaysLinkAssembly] +
       [Preserve] attributes in source (BugpunchNative/BugpunchClient + the WebRTC
       bootstrap), which IL2CPP honors directly without link.xml discovery. -->
  <assembly fullname="ODDGames.Bugpunch">
    <type fullname="WatchAttribute" preserve="all"/>
    <type fullname="WatchOwner" preserve="all"/>
  </assembly>
</linker>
